    <div class="article-section" id="overview">
      <p>The <strong>Royal Houses of the Realm</strong> are the twelve noble bloodlines formally recognized by the <a href="#" class="wikilink">High Council of Thrones</a> as holding hereditary rights within <a href="index.html" class="wikilink">Ormandia</a>. These rights include — but are not limited to — territorial sovereignty, the right to raise private armies, preferential access to positions in the <a href="#" class="wikilink">Arcane Collegium</a>, and representation on the High Council.</p>

      <p>The houses are divided into two formal tiers. The three <strong>Great Houses</strong> — Valdenmyr, Thornecroft, and Ashenvale — hold permanent seats on the High Council and bear historical precedence by virtue of their role in the founding of the Realm. The nine <strong>Noble Houses</strong> hold rotating representation and govern their respective territories with considerable but not unlimited autonomy.</p>

      <p>The relationships between houses — whether bonds of marriage, commerce, arcane alliance, or bitter rivalry — constitute the principal drama of Ormandian politics. Scholars at the <a href="#" class="wikilink">Valdenmere Academy of Statecraft</a> have famously described the web of house relations as "a living document that rewrites itself every generation."</p>
    </div>

    <!-- GREAT HOUSES -->
    <div class="article-section" id="great-houses">
      <h2>The Three Great Houses</h2>
      <div class="tier-label">⚜ Great Houses — Founding Bloodlines</div>

      <div class="great-house">
        <div class="house-entry" id="valdenmyr">
          <div class="house-header">
            <div class="house-sigil">🏰</div>
            <div class="house-title-block">
              <div class="house-name">House Valdenmyr</div>
              <div class="house-words">"The Crown Endures"</div>
            </div>
            <div class="house-country">COUNTRY<span>Valdenmere</span></div>
          </div>
          <div class="house-body">
            <p>The oldest of the Great Houses and the most politically powerful, House Valdenmyr traces its lineage directly to <a href="#" class="wikilink">King Aldric the Undying</a>, founder of the Realm. Their ancestral seat is the <a href="#" class="wikilink">Citadel of Valdenmere</a>, a fortress-palace that has never been breached in its eight centuries of existence. The Valdenmyr sigil — a golden crown on black — is recognized across the Known World as the symbol of the Realm itself.</p>
            <p>The current head of house is <strong>Queen Elowen Valdenmyr III</strong>, a politically shrewd and reportedly cold-blooded ruler who has maintained the house's position through a combination of strategic marriages, carefully engineered trade agreements, and a formidable intelligence network known informally as the <a href="#" class="wikilink">Crown's Shadow</a>. She has ruled for 22 years and shows no sign of weakening.</p>
            <p>House Valdenmyr is notable for producing a disproportionate number of skilled administrators and diplomats, but relatively few military commanders or arcane practitioners. Their power lies in governance, not force.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="house-meta">
            <div class="house-meta-item"><span class="meta-label">Current Head</span><span class="meta-value">Queen Elowen III</span></div>
            <div class="house-meta-item"><span class="meta-label">Seat</span><span class="meta-value">Citadel of Valdenmere</span></div>
            <div class="house-meta-item"><span class="meta-label">Sigil</span><span class="meta-value">Gold Crown on Black</span></div>
            <div class="house-meta-item"><span class="meta-label">Founded</span><span class="meta-value">Before Common Age</span></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="great-house">
        <div class="house-entry" id="thornecroft">
          <div class="house-header">
            <div class="house-sigil">🦌</div>
            <div class="house-title-block">
              <div class="house-name">House Thornecroft</div>
              <div class="house-words">"Through Thorn and Stone"</div>
            </div>
            <div class="house-country">COUNTRY<span>Thorneshire</span></div>
          </div>
          <div class="house-body">
            <p>House Thornecroft governs the vast agricultural heartland of <a href="countries.html" class="wikilink">Thorneshire</a> and is, by many measures, the richest house in the Realm by virtue of sheer land holdings. The Thornecrofts are famously stubborn, legendarily proud, and possessed of a cavalry tradition that has broken armies on three separate occasions. Their sigil — a black stag on grey — is considered a symbol of resilience.</p>
            <p>The house's current patriarch, <strong>Lord Aldous Thornecroft</strong>, is an elderly but sharp-minded man whose primary concern is the passing of a new grain taxation treaty that would significantly benefit Thorneshire's farmers. He is in poor health and has three children whose competing ambitions make succession a matter of considerable anxiety in the Thorneshire court.</p>
            <p>House Thornecroft maintains a tense but stable rivalry with <a href="#ironwall" class="wikilink">House Ironwall</a>, stemming from a centuries-old border dispute that technically remains unresolved. They are formally allied with <a href="#ashenvale" class="wikilink">House Ashenvale</a> through a marriage bond established two generations ago.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="house-meta">
            <div class="house-meta-item"><span class="meta-label">Current Head</span><span class="meta-value">Lord Aldous Thornecroft</span></div>
            <div class="house-meta-item"><span class="meta-label">Seat</span><span class="meta-value">Thornhold Keep</span></div>
            <div class="house-meta-item"><span class="meta-label">Sigil</span><span class="meta-value">Black Stag on Grey</span></div>
            <div class="house-meta-item"><span class="meta-label">Founded</span><span class="meta-value">~50 B.C.</span></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="great-house">
        <div class="house-entry" id="ashenvale">
          <div class="house-header">
            <div class="house-sigil">🌑</div>
            <div class="house-title-block">
              <div class="house-name">House Ashenvale</div>
              <div class="house-words">"Memory Outlasts All"</div>
            </div>
            <div class="house-country">COUNTRY<span>Ashenvale</span></div>
          </div>
          <div class="house-body">
            <p>The oldest bloodline in Ormandia, House Ashenvale's genealogical records extend back nearly a thousand years — further than any other noble family in the Known World. Scholars debate whether the house's legendary longevity is attributable to good fortune, careful record-keeping, or the hereditary arcane sensitivity that the Ashenvale bloodline indisputably carries.</p>
            <p>The current head is <strong>Queen Seraphine Ashenvale</strong>, a woman in her mid-forties who is believed by the <a href="#" class="wikilink">Arcane Collegium</a> to be one of the most naturally gifted Threadworkers alive, though she has never formally trained. She rules a country of scholars, archivists, and careful people with a patience and quiet authority that most who meet her find unsettling.</p>
            <p>House Ashenvale's primary concern in current politics is the protection of the <a href="#" class="wikilink">Deepwood Archives</a> — a vast underground repository of historical and arcane texts housed beneath their ancestral seat, <a href="#" class="wikilink">Ashencrown</a> — from what Queen Seraphine believes is an Ironmark-backed effort to access restricted arcane knowledge.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="house-meta">
            <div class="house-meta-item"><span class="meta-label">Current Head</span><span class="meta-value">Queen Seraphine</span></div>
            <div class="house-meta-item"><span class="meta-label">Seat</span><span class="meta-value">Ashencrown</span></div>
            <div class="house-meta-item"><span class="meta-label">Sigil</span><span class="meta-value">Silver Ash Tree on Black</span></div>
            <div class="house-meta-item"><span class="meta-label">Founded</span><span class="meta-value">Before Records</span></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- NOBLE HOUSES -->
    <div class="article-section" id="noble-houses">
      <h2>The Noble Houses</h2>
      <div class="tier-label">Noble Houses — Nine Recognized Bloodlines</div>

      <div class="house-entry" id="merwynd">
        <div class="house-header">
          <div class="house-sigil">⚓</div>
          <div class="house-title-block">
            <div class="house-name">House Merwynd</div>
            <div class="house-words">"Fortune Follows the Brave"</div>
          </div>
          <div class="house-country">COUNTRY<span>Craedmoor</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="house-body">
          <p>The ruling house of <a href="countries.html" class="wikilink">Craedmoor</a>, House Merwynd built its power not through conquest but commerce. Their maritime fleets control an estimated 40% of all sea trade passing through Ormandian waters. The current head, <strong>Duke Lorcan Merwynd</strong>, is a charming and ruthless negotiator who has recently brokered a controversial exclusive trading agreement with a foreign power — a move that has drawn significant criticism from the High Council.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="house-meta">
          <div class="house-meta-item"><span class="meta-label">Current Head</span><span class="meta-value">Duke Lorcan Merwynd</span></div>
          <div class="house-meta-item"><span class="meta-label">Seat</span><span class="meta-value">Harbour Reach</span></div>
          <div class="house-meta-item"><span class="meta-label">Sigil</span><span class="meta-value">Gold Anchor on Blue</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="house-entry" id="embervane">
        <div class="house-header">
          <div class="house-sigil">🔥</div>
          <div class="house-title-block">
            <div class="house-name">House Embervane</div>
            <div class="house-words">"From the Flame, Reborn"</div>
          </div>
          <div class="house-country">COUNTRY<span>Emberfall</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="house-body">
          <p>Rulers of the southern country of <a href="countries.html" class="wikilink">Emberfall</a>, House Embervane is a passionate and sometimes volatile noble family deeply intertwined with the <a href="#" class="wikilink">Six-Fold Faith</a>'s Flame Aspect. Succession crises have plagued the house for three generations; the current ruler, <strong>King Cassiel Embervane</strong>, came to power following the disputed death of his older brother and faces ongoing challenges to his legitimacy from a cousin who controls significant southern territory.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="house-meta">
          <div class="house-meta-item"><span class="meta-label">Current Head</span><span class="meta-value">King Cassiel Embervane</span></div>
          <div class="house-meta-item"><span class="meta-label">Seat</span><span class="meta-value">Char Citadel</span></div>
          <div class="house-meta-item"><span class="meta-label">Sigil</span><span class="meta-value">White Flame on Red</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="house-entry" id="sylvaran">
        <div class="house-header">
          <div class="house-sigil">🌿</div>
          <div class="house-title-block">
            <div class="house-name">House Sylvaran</div>
            <div class="house-words">"Root and Bough, We Stand"</div>
          </div>
          <div class="house-country">COUNTRY<span>Sylmara</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="house-body">
          <p>The human half of <a href="countries.html" class="wikilink">Sylmara</a>'s dual governance, House Sylvaran holds a uniquely complex position — sharing authority with the <a href="#" class="wikilink">Fae Conclave</a> and serving as the official interface between Sylmara and the rest of the Realm. Their members are often multilingual (Common, Sylvari, and High Ormanic at minimum) and unusually long-lived by human standards, a trait attributed by scholars to their centuries of proximity to Fae magic. The current co-ruler is <strong>Princess Elara Sylvaran</strong>, a young woman navigating her first decade of power with remarkable poise.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="house-meta">
          <div class="house-meta-item"><span class="meta-label">Current Head</span><span class="meta-value">Princess Elara Sylvaran</span></div>
          <div class="house-meta-item"><span class="meta-label">Seat</span><span class="meta-value">Greenbough Hall</span></div>
          <div class="house-meta-item"><span class="meta-label">Sigil</span><span class="meta-value">Silver Leaf on Green</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="house-entry" id="ironwall">
        <div class="house-header">
          <div class="house-sigil">⚔</div>
          <div class="house-title-block">
            <div class="house-name">House Ironwall</div>
            <div class="house-words">"Unbroken"</div>
          </div>
          <div class="house-country">COUNTRY<span>Ironmark</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="house-body">
          <p>Rulers of <a href="countries.html" class="wikilink">Ironmark</a> and commanders of the Realm's most feared military force, House Ironwall is a house of soldiers. For over three centuries, every head of house has held a military rank before assuming governance. The current head, <strong>Marshal-King Drevyn Ironwall</strong>, is a decorated veteran of two major border conflicts and a man widely regarded as the most dangerous individual currently seated on the High Council. His cold war with <a href="#thornecroft" class="wikilink">House Thornecroft</a> — and his suspected interest in the <a href="#" class="wikilink">Deepwood Archives</a> — are sources of significant concern to watchers of Ormandian politics.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="house-meta">
          <div class="house-meta-item"><span class="meta-label">Current Head</span><span class="meta-value">Marshal-King Drevyn</span></div>
          <div class="house-meta-item"><span class="meta-label">Seat</span><span class="meta-value">Fortress Irongate</span></div>
          <div class="house-meta-item"><span class="meta-label">Sigil</span><span class="meta-value">Black Sword on Iron</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="house-entry" id="silvermoore">
        <div class="house-header">
          <div class="house-sigil">✦</div>
          <div class="house-title-block">
            <div class="house-name">House Silvermoore</div>
            <div class="house-words">"Stars Guide the Worthy"</div>
          </div>
          <div class="house-country">COUNTRY<span>Valdenmere (Minor)</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="house-body">
          <p>A minor house by territorial standards, House Silvermoore punches far above its weight due to its extraordinary concentration of arcane talent. Based in the university city of <a href="#" class="wikilink">Spellar's Mount</a> within Valdenmere, the Silvermoores have provided more faculty members to the <a href="#" class="wikilink">Arcane Collegium</a> than any other noble house. The current head, <strong>Archmagister Lyrien Silvermoore</strong>, simultaneously holds the chairmanship of the Collegium — a combination of power that makes other houses quietly nervous.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="house-meta">
          <div class="house-meta-item"><span class="meta-label">Current Head</span><span class="meta-value">Archmagister Lyrien</span></div>
          <div class="house-meta-item"><span class="meta-label">Seat</span><span class="meta-value">Spellar's Mount</span></div>
          <div class="house-meta-item"><span class="meta-label">Sigil</span><span class="meta-value">Silver Star on Midnight Blue</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="house-entry" id="dunharrow">
        <div class="house-header">
          <div class="house-sigil">🗡</div>
          <div class="house-title-block">
            <div class="house-name">House Dunharrow</div>
            <div class="house-words">"In Shadow, Safety"</div>
          </div>
          <div class="house-country">COUNTRY<span>Ashenvale (Minor)</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="house-body">
          <p>One of the more enigmatic houses in the Realm, House Dunharrow governs a remote northern territory of Ashenvale known for its moors, its ancient standing stones, and an unusually high rate of arcane incidents. The house keeps few public records, maintains minimal presence at the High Council, and is periodically the subject of dark rumours — few of which have ever been substantiated. The current head's name is recorded in Compact documents as <strong>Lord Caelan Dunharrow</strong>, though he has not been seen publicly in seven years.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="house-meta">
          <div class="house-meta-item"><span class="meta-label">Current Head</span><span class="meta-value">Lord Caelan Dunharrow</span></div>
